The Garden Tapes: The Song Remains The Same Concerts (Expanded And Revisited Collector's Edition) is Empress Valley's newest deluxe title collecting all available sources from July 27th to 29th, 1973 recorded during final thre nights of ninth US tour in New York. This large set covering both audience and soundboard sources for all three nights, also adding so called bonus discs to the July 28th and July 29th dates from alternate board feed.
Having in mind these dates are one of themost important live dates in group's live repertoire and fact for the very first time all dates are sourced from upgraded and previously unreleased sources making this production a very interesting and worthy gem.
